To the Editor:
To many people, the basic problem at Grin<
hell is not open forms, BELG, or the hall system, but the spirit and atmosphere of the college me, both academic and social. final to
all colleges in general and the small liberal
arts college in particular is an active (3011‘
com on the part of the students for what they
are doing and what is happening around
them. A number of other colleges have many
of the same aspects as Grinnell — size, rules,
inclusion —- but have much different atmosphere. What these schools have that Grinnell
does not have are student bodies which are
aware. excited, and available. It is this lack
of vibrator and excitement which is basic to
the Grinnell campus problem.
What we need is an hiring of emotions and
an intellectual interactive of those topics
which should be important to us — the role
at the student in the community, the active
process of learning, current events, speakers,
concerts, and everything else which we should
be concerned about.
The 5&3 has a direct function and respond elite in the formation of such a specialized atmosphere. As the ideal medium—
in terms of format and distribution—the 5853
should carry on discussions arising from colluqlliurns. review stimulating events, and pose
discussions 0! the'ideas and questions involved. Discussion is a direct step toward an
environment where there is an excited interactive and conﬂict of ideas, and outdoors. The
Shit should are-evaluate its role in the building of an active and library Grinnell.
