and the aging actor. A precise sense of timing
made their performances especially removable.
Ruthie Sternberg, who portraits the cute.
was grateful and exact.
when the cast was taking its certain call.
they turned to applied Anne robinson and
Janet Hamilton for their accompaniment at
the piano and harpsicord. I thank them too.
In general. the comic parts of the show
were the best, and the romantic scenes, the
nearest. But this last price is more an argument with the script than the production.
The cast may have been steven in talent,
but all of them shared in the spirit at the
show. We knew they were enjoying it and this
increased our own pleasure. Rick MacDoweit.
the operator, was outstanding. His is a
physically evaluating role’and i was amazon
that he never seemed out of breath. Rick's
title movements, his strong voice and the
Mephistophelean print in his eyes beautifully
